article.headline: Hawaii 71, San Jose State 45
article.story: HONOLULU (AP) -- Vaidotas Peciukas came off the bench to lead Hawaii with 13 points as the Rainbow Warriors beat the San Jose State Spartans 71-45 Saturday night. Hawaii (9-2, 1-2 Western Athletic Conference) outscored San Jose State 14-2, including four consecutive dunks, in the first eight minutes of the game on its way to a 32-13 halftime lead. Matt Gibson added 12 points for the Rainbow Warriors and teammate Julian Sensley had a double-double with 10 points and 11 rebounds. San Jose State (3-9, 0-3) went on a 14-2 run midway through the second half to pull to within 15. But the Rainbow Warriors responded with a 14-1 run of their own and Peciukas scored 12 of his 13 points in the final eight minutes to seal the Hawaii victory. The Rainbow Warriors, who held a height advantage at every position, outrebounded the smaller Spartans 44-25. Marquin Chandler led San Jose State with 15 points and eight rebounds and Donta Watson added 12. The Spartans shot a season-low 25 percent from the field, including just 18.2 percent in the first half. Their 13 first-half points were their fewest in a half this season.
